This paper is about developing taggers for extracting adverse drug reactions and related entities using a mix of rule-based, machine learning, and deep learning methodologies. The paper focuses on natural language processing and information extraction, which are core topics in the computer science sub-categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL), machine learning (cs.LG), information retrieval (cs.IR), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), and cybernetics (cs.CY).
